            <h2>Keeping it Local</h2>

            <p>
                It is no secret that Windsorites love their pizza, and the proof is not just in the reviews but in the numbers. Windsor has at least 62 locally owned and operated pizzerias that all follow Windsor-style pizza. In comparison, there are only 46 big chain pizzerias, which include Domino’s, Little Caesars, Pizza Pizza, Pizza Depot, Pizza Hut, Red Swan, and Boston Pizza.
            </p>

            <p>
                According to Joe Carivino, owner of Antonino’s Pizza, “Windsor-Essex may have more pizza eaters than anywhere else in North America, but their tastes are very discerning… national chains close locations here and sometimes pull out of the market completely.”
            </p>

        </div>

